        ii.
            [{{c1::Faster data transfer over short distances; Can send multiple bits simultaneously; Simple implementation for short links::What are the advantages of parallel transmission?}}]
            [{{c1::Prone to interference and crosstalk; Limited to short distances; Bulkier and more expensive cabling::What are the disadvantages of parallel transmission?}}] [{{c1::Reliable over long distances; Less interference and crosstalk; Cheaper and simpler cabling::What are the advantages of serial transmission?}}] [{{c1::Slower than parallel for short distances; Sends one bit at a time; May require more complex timing mechanisms::What are the disadvantages of serial transmission?}}] [{{c1::Simple and cost-effective; Easy to implement; No need for complex coordination::What are the advantages of simplex communication?}}] [{{c1::One-way communication only; No feedback or error correction from receiver; Inefficient for interactive systems::What are the disadvantages of simplex communication?}}] [{{c1::Allows two-way communication (not simultaneous); More efficient than simplex; Shares a single channel::What are the advantages of half-duplex communication?}}] [{{c1::Cannot send and receive at the same time; Possible delays when switching direction; Lower efficiency than full duplex::What are the disadvantages of half-duplex communication?}}] [{{c1::Simultaneous two-way communication; More efficient and faster; No waiting for transmission turns::What are the advantages of full-duplex communication?}}] [{{c1::More complex and expensive to implement; Requires more bandwidth or separate channels; Higher power usage::What are the disadvantages of full-duplex communication?}}]
    